description:
## Bug Report

Please answer these questions before submitting your issue. Thanks!

This bug has been fixed by #55537 in v8.5.0 and nightly, but it affects previous LTS versions.

### 1. Minimal reproduce step (Required)

<!-- a step by step guide for reproducing the bug. -->

1. Prepare the inconsistency in v7.5.4 (use a known bug, see issue 52510).

```bash
tiup cluster deploy debug v7.5.4 debug.toml
tiup cluster start debug
```

```sql
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `t`;
CREATE TABLE `t` (
  `id` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `pid` varchar(255) NOT NULL,
  `created_at` datetime NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`) /*T![clustered_index] CLUSTERED */
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_unicode_ci ;

INSERT INTO `t` (`id`, `pid`, `created_at`) VALUES
('o', 'productA', '2023-10-01 12:00:00'),
('1', 'productB', '2023-10-02 13:30:00'),
('oO', 'productC', '2023-10-03 14:45:00'),
('0', 'productD', '2023-10-04 15:20:00'),
('child5', 'productE', '2023-10-05 16:10:00');

CREATE INDEX t_idx_created_at ON t (created_at);
```

2. Run admin check in v7.5.4

```sql
mysql> SET SESSION tidb_enable_fast_table_check=ON;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)
mysql> ADMIN CHECK TABLE t;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.01 sec)

mysql> SET SESSION tidb_enable_fast_table_check=OFF;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)
mysql> ADMIN CHECK TABLE t;
ERROR 1105 (HY000): runtime error: index out of range [2] with length 2

mysql> SELECT * FROM t FORCE INDEX(t_idx_created_at);
ERROR 1105 (HY000): runtime error: index out of range [2] with length 2
```


3. Run admin check and a index scan in the latest LTS versions (v7.5.6, v8.1.2, v8.5.0, nightly)

```bash
tiup cluster upgrade debug v... --force
```

```sql
SET SESSION tidb_enable_fast_table_check=ON;
ADMIN CHECK TABLE t;
SET SESSION tidb_enable_fast_table_check=OFF;
ADMIN CHECK TABLE t;
SELECT * FROM t FORCE INDEX(t_idx_created_at);
```

### 2. What did you expect to see? (Required)

Regardless of whatever the value of tidb_enable_fast_table_check is set, `ADMIN CHECK` should return the same result.

### 3. What did you see instead (Required)

Incorrect result in v7.5.6 and v8.1.2
```sql
mysql> SET SESSION tidb_enable_fast_table_check=ON;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)
mysql> ADMIN CHECK TABLE t;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.01 sec)

mysql> SET SESSION tidb_enable_fast_table_check=OFF;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)
mysql> ADMIN CHECK TABLE t;
ERROR 1105 (HY000): runtime error: index out of range [2] with length 2

mysql> SELECT * FROM t FORCE INDEX(t_idx_created_at);
ERROR 1105 (HY000): runtime error: index out of range [2] with length 2
```

Correct v8.5.0 and nightly

```sql
mysql> SET SESSION tidb_enable_fast_table_check=ON;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)
mysql> ADMIN CHECK TABLE t;
ERROR 1105 (HY000): checkIndexTask panicked, indexOffset: 0

mysql> SET SESSION tidb_enable_fast_table_check=OFF;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)
mysql> ADMIN CHECK TABLE t;
ERROR 1105 (HY000): runtime error: index out of range [2] with length 2

mysql> SELECT * FROM t FORCE INDEX(t_idx_created_at);
ERROR 1105 (HY000): runtime error: index out of range [2] with length 2
```

### 4. What is your TiDB version? (Required)

<!-- Paste the output of SELECT tidb_version() -->
- v7.5.6
- v8.1.2
